action.text:
Already 6 feet tall, Brian Sanchez decided to gain 7 more inches through double limb-lengthening surgery—not for height itself, but because he felt his proportions were off. The 33-year-old mortgage broker from Georgia compared his natural build to the "Thumb Thumbs" from Spy Kids, believing his legs were too short for his torso.

Two separate procedures in Turkey at the Live Life Taller clinic—one breaking and extending his tibia and fibula in December 2022, another lengthening his femurs in March 2023—brought him to nearly 6'7". Total investment: $106,000.

His wife Nidia, standing at 5'10", now has a drastically different view when they're together. While critics questioned why someone already above average height would pursue such extreme measures, Sanchez expressed complete satisfaction with his decision and new perspective.

The story, discussed on The Joe Rogan Experience with Derek from More Plates More Dates, raises questions about where personal body autonomy meets unconventional choices. @thejrecompanion breaks down the full conversation in the episode links.
